{"article_id":"QBB78rhPDfQ705bc","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Administration officials view Rice as something of an interventionist .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"| REUTERS","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"Why Obama picked Rice","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"Since Rahm Emanuel packed his bags ,","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"President Barack Obama has recruited senior staffers","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"who mirror his regimented , stay-in-your-lane style -","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"but his choice of Susan Rice as National Security Adviser represents a shift back to the days","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"when the West Wing brimmed with big ideas and even bigger egos .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"In picking the lightning-rod U.N . Ambassador","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"to replace the lower-key , process-driven Tom Donilon ,","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"Obama has broken with recent history","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"to tap a colorful , ideological","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"- and ultimately unpredictable -","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"replacement , a move","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"geared at energizing the White House","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"and crafting a more coherent Obama Doctrine","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"that moves beyond \" leading from behind . \"","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"Rice is a genuine wild card ,","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"people close to the situation say :","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"Major questions loom about Rice ' s capacity","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"to deal with the congressional Republicans","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"who blocked her appointment as secretary of state over the Benghazi fiasco","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"and her ability","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"to negotiate the claustrophobic West Wing .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"Above all , it remains to be seen if Rice can sell the deeply cautious Obama team on a more interventionist , human-rights focused vision of U.S. power projection","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"- an approach","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"Rice has , for the moment , ruled out in Syria .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"\" Despite the Benghazi thing , I expect Susan to be more of a public presence","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"than Tom has been in terms of speeches , news briefings and even TV , \"","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"said Tommy Vietor , a former NSC spokesman","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"who worked for Donilon .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"\" She ' s smart ,","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"she doesn ' t mess around","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"- and she ' s tough . ...","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"There are not a lot of goofy , affable national security advisers . \"","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"Rice ' s former spokesman at the U.N. Mark Kornblau painted a very different portrait of Rice than the quiet , publicity-averse Donilon ,","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"who carefully monitors the flow of information to Obama , a commander-in-chief","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"who prefers his foreign policy to lay out all arguments","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"rather than advocating any single one .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"\" Susan , \"","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"said Kornblau ,","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"\" has has the vision","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"to set the right strategic course ,","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"the sheer will","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"to grind it out","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"to get there...","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"Plus , she ' s usually about two steps ahead of everyone else in the room . \"","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"Another former administration official put it more bluntly :","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"\" She sometimes doesn ' t play well with others ,","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"and that could shake things up a bit . \"","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"That might be just what Obama wants right now .","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"Facing months of GOP intransigence and investigations ,","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"has recently made a series of appointments to his administration and the bench","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"that reflect his personal preference","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"- and need","depth":15},{"id":55,"text":"to fire up the Democratic base for the fights ahead -","depth":15},{"id":56,"text":"more than steering a middle course","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"geared at attracting bipartisan support .","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"And unlike other recent high-profile picks , he ' s gone with someone in Rice","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"who ' s known more for independence","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"than getting along .","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"\" Susan is the consummate public servant , a patriot","depth":15},{"id":62,"text":"who puts her country first .","depth":15},{"id":63,"text":"She is fearless ,","depth":15},{"id":64,"text":"she is tough ,","depth":16},{"id":65,"text":"she has a great tennis game and a pretty good basketball game , \"","depth":16},{"id":66,"text":"Obama said ,","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"flanked by Rice and Samantha Power , the anti-genocide crusader","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"he tapped","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"to replace the 48-year-old Rice at the United Nations .","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"\" Her brother is here ,","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"who I play with occasionally .","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"It runs in the family ,","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"throwing the occasional elbow","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"but hitting the big shot , \"","depth":14},{"id":75,"text":"alluding to Rice ' s well-known pugnacity","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"- which may put her at odds with Secretary of State John Kerry ,","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"who got the job","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"she had been heading for .","depth":14},{"id":79,"text":"CORRECTION :","depth":4},{"id":80,"text":"Corrected by :","depth":5},{"id":81,"text":"Nick Gass @ 06/06/2013 11:33 PM","depth":5},{"id":82,"text":"CORRECTION :","depth":4},{"id":83,"text":"An earlier version of this story misstated the position","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"Susan Rice was serving in during the 1994 Rwanda genocide .","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"She was an NSC staffer .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":171,"left":87,"right":170,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":87,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":163,"right":169,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":2,"right":162,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":162,"left":110,"right":161,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":110,"left":100,"right":109,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":91,"right":99,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":91,"left":89,"right":90,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":89,"left":3,"right":88,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":88,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":90,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":92,"right":98,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":92,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":10,"right":97,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":94,"right":96,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":93,"right":13,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":93,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":95,"right":16,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":109,"left":101,"right":108,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":108,"left":105,"right":107,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":105,"left":103,"right":104,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{